FOR PYTHON 2 ENVIRONMENT

#COMMANDS

>>> pip2 install virtualenv

>>> virtualenv my_env1 

source my_env1/bin/activate
--------------------------
INSTALL DJANGO

#COMMANDS

>>> pip2 install django

# From the command line, cd into a directory where you’d like to store your code, then run the following command:

>>> django-admin startproject mysite

This will create a mysite directory in your current directory.

Change into the outer mysite directory

>>> python manage.py runserver

You’ve started the Django development server, a lightweight Web server written purely in Python.

To create your app, make sure you’re in the same directory as manage.py and type this command:

>>> python manage.py startapp app_name
------------------------------------------
if (Error: That port is already in use.)

>>> sudo fuser -k 8000/tcp
